          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Understand management definition",
            "Identify core functions of management"
          ],
          "content": "## Introduction to Management\nManagement is the process of planning, organizing, leading, and controlling resources to achieve organizational goals efficiently and effectively.\n\n### Efficiency vs Effectiveness\n- Efficiency: Minimizing waste\n- Effectiveness: Achieving goals\n\n### Functions of Management\n- Planning\n- Organizing\n- Leading\n- Controlling\n\n### Role of Managers\nManagers coordinate people and resources to achieve organizational objectives.\n\n### Example\nA production manager allocating resources and monitoring output demonstrates all management functions.",
          "examples": [
            "Factory production planning",
            "Team management in IT company"
          ],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Confusing efficiency with effectiveness",
            "Ignoring planning stage"
          ],
          "qna": [
            {
              "q": "What is management?",
              "a": "Process of planning, organizing, leading, controlling resources."
            },
            {
              "q": "What is efficiency?",
              "a": "Doing things with minimal waste."
            },
            { "q": "What is effectiveness?", "a": "Achieving desired goals." },
            {
              "q": "Functions of management?",
              "a": "Planning, organizing, leading, controlling."
            },
            { "q": "Example?", "a": "Managing factory production." }
          ]
        },
        {
          "topic_id": "t2",
          "title": "Managerial Roles",
          "difficulty": "medium",
          "estimated_time": "15 min",
          "prerequisites": ["t1"],
          "learning_outcomes": [
            "Understand Mintzberg roles",
            "Apply managerial responsibilities"
          ],
          "content": "## Managerial Roles\nManagers perform different roles categorized into interpersonal, informational, and decisional roles.\n\n### Interpersonal Roles\n- Leader\n- Liaison\n\n### Informational Roles\n- Monitor\n- Disseminator\n\n### Decisional Roles\n- Entrepreneur\n- Negotiator\n\n### Importance\nUnderstanding roles improves leadership effectiveness.",
          "examples": ["Manager negotiating deals", "Leader motivating team"],
          "common_mistakes": [
            "Ignoring communication role",
            "Over-focusing on authority"
          ],
          "qna": [
            { "q": "Who proposed managerial roles?", "a": "Henry Mintzberg." },
            { "q": "Types?", "a": "Interpersonal, informational, decisional." },
            { "q": "Leader role?", "a": "Motivating employees." },
            { "q": "Negotiator role?", "a": "Handling agreements." },
            { "q": "Why important?", "a": "Improves effectiveness." }
          ]
        }
      ]
    },
